C. DIFFERENCES IN FORM 1. NOUNS AND PRONOUNS

a) Differences in Number: In 1:20 and 3: 15 the Latin versions have both the singular and the plural forms where the LXX has the singular; in 3: 14, 16, 173 2615 the Latin has both numbers, while the LXX has the plural.

b) Difference in Gender: In 1: 5 and 17:12 dies is masculine in one version and feminine in the other.
